= Authentication and Authorization =

== Authentication Modes ==
Pulse uses split auth models by runtime surface:

=== Web Authentication (Pulse.Web) ===
* OWIN application cookie + forms/session behavior
* Logged-in users can mint API JWT via web auth endpoint
* JWT is attached by client script using an AJAX prefilter approach

=== API Authentication (Pulse.Api) ===
* JWT bearer token validation for API endpoints
* Token settings are shared through '''Jwt:*''' configuration values

== Authorization Model ==
Authorization is claims-driven using module code claims (for example: module-specific VIEW/ADD/EDIT/DELETE).

=== Enforcement Surfaces ===
* MVC: Authorize filter for module claims
* API: Authorize filter for module claims
* UI helpers: claim-based visibility for links and actions

== Membership-Scoped Access ==
Access is not only claim-based; plant/project membership also gates behavior:
* Active plant members can open project index and details for projects within plant scope.
* Project members or owners can access deeper project mutation workflows (overview, review, quick edit, etc.).

== Notable Authorization Patterns ==
* Read/list/get routes should enforce matching '''*VIEW''' module.
* Mutation routes should enforce matching add/edit/delete module.
* Plant-specific user-group assignment uses plant editor permissions to avoid requiring global user-group admin rights.

== Logout Pattern ==
Logout should route through web auth controller action:
# Sign out OWIN application cookie
# Clear forms/session state
# Redirect to configured SSO logout URL with target resource pointing back to app login

